03/04/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro agreed to advance the refugee returns process by the end of this year, during a meeting gathering the three ministers for human rights and refugees in Sarajevo on Friday (31 March). 
Representatives of the UN High Commissioner for Refugees, the European Commission and the OSCE also attended the meeting. 
Talks focused on the implementation of the 1998 Sarajevo Declaration for refugees' returns, as well as future measures to be taken. 
(Dnevni avaz - 01/04/06; PBS BiH, HRT - 31/03/06)
